Sentencas: Cathode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells (CS-T-SOFCs) have been regarded as promising energy conversion devices; however, their commercialization is blocked by high manufacturing cost and poor electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Improvement of Cathode Support Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In our group, dip-coating and co-sintering techniques were used in order to reduce the cost.
Titulo: Improvement of Cathode Support Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this paper, it was found that the degree of co-sintering significantly affected on the electrodes and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Improvement of Cathode Support Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As a result, the maximum power density of the CS-T-SOFC reached 740, 635 and 489 mW center dot cm-2 at 850, 800 and 750 degrees C respectively, with hydrogen as the fuel.
Titulo: Improvement of Cathode Support Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The stability of the improved CS-T-SOFC was also investigated.
Titulo: Improvement of Cathode Support Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
